[[Translation:en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Musicdriver]]
* '''null''': Disables music
* '''dmusic''': Enables DirectMusic. This is the default music driver on windows.
* '''win32''': Configures OpenTTD to use the system default Midi device<sup>1</sup>. 
* '''extmidi''': Enables an external midi device, from the sound cards midi/game port
* '''bemidi''': Enables the BeOS MIDI driver


=== Notes ===
*<sup>1</sup>: Depending on the Windows operating system, the default midi device may be changed via the Sounds and Audio Devices(Windows XP) or via third party tools such as Vista Midi Picker or Bassmididrv on Windows Vista/7.